Genk manager, Hannes Wolf, has confirmed that striker, Paul Onuachu, will resume training on Friday after recovering from the coronavirus. DAILY POST had reported that the Nigerian international had tested positive for COVID-19. The 26-year-old who missed his side’s friendly win against Royal Union Saint-Gilloise on Wednesday will be available for their next friendly fixture against Excelsior after his second COVID-19 test returned negative. Speaking on the development, Wolf told Het Nieuwsblad, “On Friday, he will just train with the group. “Paul can also compete against Excelsior on Friday in the exhibition match.” Onuachu scored ten goals and provided two assists in 29 appearances in all competitions in his first season at Genk. He joined Genk from FC Midtjylland for €6million in 2019.